#IAM
manage users and levels of access (USERS, GROUPS, ROLES (create role assign to resources), Policy (USER/GROUP/ROLE))
central control
share access
granular
Identity federation (AD, Facebook, LinkedIn)
MFA
Temporary access
Password rotation policy PCI DSS compliant



#IAM EXAM TIPS
Policies written in JSON
{"Version":"2010-10-17",
 "Statement":
 [
  {"Effect":"Allow",
   "Action":"*",
   "Resource":"*"}
 ]
 }

 IAM is Global
 USERS have no permissions when created
 Access Key & Secret Access Key used to access from CLI API
